storyInfo: Leto's mother is planning her next outdoor adventure after her condition has stabilized, but the usually easy-going Leto raises a rare objection, and so Tatyana proposes to play a game with her daughter.

attributes.content: A game?
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: That's right.
attributes.name: Tatyana

attributes.content: You don't want Mamochka to leave for her adventure, right? I don't want to make my darling crybaby weep by vanishing into thin air either, so let's play a little game.
attributes.name: Tatyana

attributes.content: I'm not a crybaby!
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Really?
attributes.name: Tatyana

attributes.content: I remember the wailing at our reunion on the landship bridge, isn't that what you'd call a—
attributes.name: Tatyana

attributes.content: Stop, stop, stop! It's not like I'm trying to keep you from stepping out, but you haven't fully recovered yet! So what's with the game?
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Oripathy can't be cured, so what even counts as 'fully recovered'?
attributes.name: Tatyana

attributes.content: But...
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: I know you're concerned about me, but the best medicine for us adventurers is always a sight we've never seen before.
attributes.name: Tatyana

attributes.content: Most importantly, do you think you could really stop me from going if I really wanted to?
attributes.name: Tatyana

attributes.content: Fine, I get it.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: So, what game is this?
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: A simple one. Hide and seek.
attributes.name: Tatyana

attributes.content: Tomorrow, I'll hide somewhere on the ship. Find me in the afternoon, and I'll stay.
attributes.name: Tatyana

attributes.content: But if you don't, you have to give up on trying to stop me.
attributes.name: Tatyana

attributes.content: Well?
attributes.name: Tatyana

attributes.content: Hey, this landship is humongous!
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: You can ask anyone to help you out. Does that make it fair?
attributes.name: Tatyana

attributes.content: Aw—fine!
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: I'll go pack up my luggage then. You should get an early night, lapochka.
attributes.name: Tatyana

attributes.content: Hmph, don't get too happy yet. I'll definitely find you.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Now that's my daughter. I'll be waiting for you.
attributes.name: Tatyana

attributes.content: Alright, better get an early night.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: I have to find Mamochka tomorrow.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Oh, I should probably message the gang before I sleep.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: 'Look out for my mamochka tomorrow. More deets in the cafeteria.'
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Alright, sent.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Sheesh, Mamochka makes me look like a good girl by comparison.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Time to snooze.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.text: Mamochka, are you going out again?
\nYes, be good at your aunt's place. Mamochka will bring you a souvenir.
I want to go with you.
\nNo can do. It's too dangerous for you. When you're older and stronger, I'll take you along with me.
\nReally?
\nOf course, I promise.

attributes.content: Didn't see her.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Yeah, figured.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: What's that supposed to mean?!
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: I'm afraid I didn't see her either.
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: Aren't you pretty chummy with her?
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: We occasionally exchange makeup tips, that's all.
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: What about you, Anna?
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Sorry.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Lada... forget it, I'm guessing you didn't see Mamochka either. Seems like she's serious about this.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Huh? I saw her.
attributes.name: Gummy

attributes.content: What?!
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Yeah, she came pretty early for breakfast.
attributes.name: Gummy

attributes.content: You should've told me!
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: But you were still sleeping. Also, you didn't tell me to let you know ASAP.
attributes.name: Gummy

attributes.content: Ugh, fine.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Did she mention where she was headed?
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: I was cooking then, so I didn't really catch it... but I heard her mention Instructor Dobermann.
attributes.name: Gummy

attributes.content: Instructor Dobermann? Come to think of it, she is helping Mamochka with her rehab.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Thanks. Let me know if anything else happens—
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Just a moment.
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: Huh?
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: You have yet to explain to us what's going on.
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: Ugh, fine.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Huh. So it's just a game? I thought something serious was going down.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: It's not just a game! If I lose, Mamochka's going out on her adventure!
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Why not let her go? Wouldn't it be good for her?
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: You're asking why? Mamochka has Oripathy, you know.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: But—she showed us her physical results last time we ate together, and said her condition's stable now.
attributes.name: Gummy

attributes.content: Even so, you can't just take off right away, right?!
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Anna's, what's with that look?
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Nothing. I just thought it was quite strange to hear that coming from your mouth, when you're the flightiest one here.
attributes.name: Istina

attributes.content: Agh, anyway, just let me know if you see her before dinner!
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: I'll head over to Instructor Dobermann first.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Rosalind becomes a totally different person the moment you bring up her mother.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: It's the one thing she's guilty about, after all.
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: Gospozha Tatyana Larina contracted Oripathy on her account, so it's no wonder she's rather hung up about it.
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: But—
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Do you think Gospozha Larina requires our concern?
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: Fine... she probably wouldn't back down even with all of us united.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: So, let's just help Rosalind out, and leave the rest to them.
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: Instructor Dobermann!
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Morning, Leto.
attributes.name: Dobermann

attributes.content: Did you see my mamochka today?
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Señora Tatyana? I did see her earlier.
attributes.name: Dobermann

attributes.content: Is she still around?
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: No, we only had a brief chat before she left, probably went to get ready for her trip.
attributes.name: Dobermann

attributes.content: Did she talk about anything else besides that?
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: I think she knew you'd come here, and asked me to pass this to you.
attributes.name: Dobermann

attributes.content: These are—?
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Climbing ropes.
attributes.name: Dobermann

attributes.content: Is this what she usually uses?
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Yes. Well, you have your own classes and missions, so it's no surprise this is new information to you.
attributes.name: Dobermann

attributes.content: Señora Tatyana may not be exceptionally strong, but she is extremely nimble. She holds the record for scaling that wall over there.
attributes.name: Dobermann

attributes.content: Can I try too?
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: I figured you'd ask. Come with me.
attributes.name: Dobermann

attributes.content: Alright, the rope's set. Go ahead.
attributes.name: Dobermann

attributes.content: Mamochka probably hid something on top of the wall, if she left these ropes for me.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Right, just watch me climb this quick and we'll see what she's hiding up there!
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Hup!
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Uwaa!
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Rock climbing isn't as simple as it looks. You have to find your fulcrum and control your balance. It's not something you can brute force your way through.
attributes.name: Dobermann

attributes.content: Again!
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: I got it! The next one—
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: I can't reach that one at all!
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: You have to propel yourself up with your momentum. You shouldn't be standing on that hold either.
attributes.name: Dobermann

attributes.content: Momentum?
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Oh—I get it!
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Again!
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Hah, so that's the way!
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Heheh, half way up now!
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Next one! Watch me!
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Damn!
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Uaaagh!
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: That was dangerous, but no matter. Just a little more to go!
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: If I want to go up from here, you'd normally step on this hold, and then climb up from there.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Hm? Seems like it'd be faster if I use this other one—
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Hehe, let's give it a shot!
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Watch me!
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Heh! Safe and sound!
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Now let's see—
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Aha, I knew it.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: A book quietly sits on the platform at the top of the climbing wall.
Leto makes her way over and realizes she has seen this book before.
She picks up the book and walks to the platform's edge. She has a good view of the entire training room from this spot.
But, she suddenly gets a feeling—
What Mamochka saw while sitting here was definitely not the training room, but some scenery etched into her mind.
Because the book she just picked up is a travel magazine—with an article mentioned on the cover written by her mother.

attributes.text: Mamochka, what's this?
\nA travel magazine. Mamochka has an article published in it.
An article?
\nMhm. My job is to turn my adventures into essays. Look, this is a photo from my last expedition.
Wow, it's pretty.
\nRight? This is how I keep us fed. It used to be something I had the most fun doing, but now, I have to work as hard as I can for the both of us.
Mamochka, you should take it easy.
\nDon't you worry. I'm happy going to these places, just like I'm happy when you're with me. Oh, how nice it'd be if we could go discover a new place together one day!
Yeah, I want to go together with you, Mamochka!
\nHaha, you'll have to grow up big and strong first, little Roza!

attributes.content: Leto, did you find something?
attributes.name: Dobermann

attributes.content: Technically yes, but also no...
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: This magazine—
attributes.name: Dobermann

attributes.content: Her travel article's in it.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Leto, do you resent your mother for not staying with you?
attributes.name: Dobermann

attributes.content: Well... Mamochka travels a lot, so it's true she isn't with me much, but her absence feels different from me not having a father.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Because Mamochka always comes home with a ton of interesting stories for me.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Words I've never heard before, sights I've never seen—Hearing Mamochka talk about all that stuff is much more interesting than if she were to just stay with me.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: I see.
attributes.name: Dobermann

attributes.content: And that's why you're so hung up on this. Both you and Señora Tatyana have always had an extraordinary mother-daughter relationship.
attributes.name: Dobermann

attributes.content: But Oripathy has tied a knot in your bond.
attributes.name: Dobermann

attributes.content: Mhm.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: I know what Mamochka wants, and I know it's the best for both of us, and yet—
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: She wouldn't be sick if she didn't go into Chernobog to find me.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: I just can't manage to convince myself.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Which is why I try to stop her from going out on adventures instead.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: I know how exactly I could keep her here, but I actually don't want her to stay.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: She'll understand you, I'm sure.
attributes.name: Dobermann

attributes.content: She wouldn't be playing this game with you otherwise, no?
attributes.name: Dobermann

attributes.content: I think she's prepared an answer for you.
attributes.name: Dobermann

attributes.content: ...Yeah.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Rosalind, I did a little investigating. It seems your mother has left a lot of smokescreens around.
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: I don't think you'll find her in time, if you check them one-by-one.
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: Are there any unusual clues she might have left you?
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: Unusual...?
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: From what I know about Mamochka, she'd definitely leave me some hint in this kinda game...
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Really?
attributes.name: Tatyana

attributes.content: I remember the wailing at our reunion on the landship bridge, isn't that what you'd call a—
attributes.name: Tatyana

attributes.content: Ah!
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: I got it!
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: You got it?
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: Oh, the bridge!
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.text: Rosalind, my lapochka!
\nMamochka?! Wh-What are you doing here?!

I heard something happened in Chernobog and came as soon as I could, but the place was already in ruins by the time I arrived. I couldn't find you no matter how hard I tried, but I'm so glad you're not hurt!
\nHeheh, why would I be? But how did you even end up here, Mamochka?
Well... it's a long story. Anyway, I heard from a Rhodes Island doctor that you were here.
\nWhy would Rhodes Island—Wait, Mamochka?! Those crystals—Why do you have Oripathy?!
\nAh. Oopsies. I-it's nothing, really. Don't worry, your Mamochka was just careless—
...Mamochka, did you get sick because of me?
\nN-No, it was from an adventure...
\nMa... it's all my fault—
Oh, don't cry. A little illness is nothing, as long as you're okay.
\n*sob* Uwaaaaaaah———!

attributes.content: Mamochka talked about when she first arrived at Rhodes Island! I should've connected the dots last night!
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: I turned into a sobbing mess while hugging my mamochka right here!
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: But I don't see anyone else here?
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: Oh, Leto and Rosa. What are you girls doing up here?
attributes.name: Human Resources Operator

attributes.content: Have you seen my mamochka?
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Hm? Tatyana? Can't say I have.
attributes.name: Human Resources Operator

attributes.content: Hmph.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: But she did leave a bag here, and I was worrying over it. Why don't you hand it back to her?
attributes.name: Human Resources Operator

attributes.content: Huh?
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Lemme take a look!
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Over here, it's pretty heavy.
attributes.name: Human Resources Operator

attributes.content: This is—
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: A brand new outdoor camping set, and a book series on polyglot secrets?
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: Hmph. She had me figured out, and knew I would come here.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Huh? There's a letter too.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: 'For my dear daughter'. Whoa, she even drew a smiley. It's mocking me.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Gospozha Larina would indeed do such a thing, knowing her.
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: You should open it.
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: Lapochka, your aunt told me I should be spending more time with you.
But you know how I am. I'm well aware I'm not doing a great job as a mother—I've tried, but in the end, I felt it was impossible.
I've agonized over this for a long time, but the one who sweeps all the agony away is you.
You always greet me when I come home, with your smile full of anticipation and joy washing all my anxieties away.
You eagerly listen to every tale I tell you.
The funny school stories you tell me always make me laugh out loud.
You tell me with your actions—it's alright for me to act like this, and we can base our relationship on that.
You don't know this, but it's a way for Mamochka to redeem herself, and I'm not exaggerating.
Because this means I can love both you and my work.
Of course, we have fun together, but when we're apart, I'll be happy if I know you are too. And you'll be happy if you know I'm happy.
Isn't this how we've been the last few years?
I know you feel guilt over my Oripathy, and that's why you're always volunteering to see those sights in my stead.
But losing you is what I fear most. As long as you're healthy and happy, this illness isn't much at all.
And now, we've both found our own meaningful paths to walk on, in a sense.
So, I hope you can look after your own life better, just like you have in the past.
Become a beacon, just like 'General Leto'.
And likewise, your Mamochka will take good care of herself.
Alright?
My daughter should have found the letter by now.
attributes.name: Tatyana

attributes.content: Even if she didn't, someone else will, and they'll have passed it to her.
attributes.name: Tatyana

attributes.content: Don't blame Mamochka, lapochka.
attributes.name: Tatyana

attributes.content: We've never needed so many words between us, right?
attributes.name: Tatyana

attributes.content: Being your daughter's hardly the easiest job in the world.
attributes.name: Asbestos

attributes.content: Ah, here you are, little Asbest.
attributes.name: Tatyana

attributes.content: You can drop the 'little'. I insist.
attributes.name: Asbestos

attributes.content: You never intended to let your daughter find you in the first place, huh?
attributes.name: Asbestos

attributes.content: She is dear to me, but so are my adventures.
attributes.name: Tatyana

attributes.content: This aircraft is a part of Rhodes Island, so I technically didn't lie to her, did I?
attributes.name: Tatyana

attributes.content: As it goes in the family—we always mean what we say!
attributes.name: Tatyana

attributes.content: Suit yourself. I just think it's pretty miserable for her.
attributes.name: Asbestos

attributes.content: Just you wait. You'll understand in the future when you find your own fork in your path, little Asbest.
attributes.name: Tatyana

attributes.content: Heh, the only future I see is dying on an expedition.
attributes.name: Asbestos

attributes.content: What a coincidence. I used to think the same.
attributes.name: Tatyana

attributes.content: For real though, why didn't you go looking for Magallan? Why tag along with me?
attributes.name: Asbestos

attributes.content: The route little Maggy was taking does have its charms, but I still prefer a more challenging environment.
attributes.name: Tatyana

attributes.content: Don't you think our tastes are pretty similar in that regard?
attributes.name: Tatyana

attributes.content: Hmph, I should've dumped you here and set off on my own.
attributes.name: Asbestos

attributes.content: The Doctor would be sad to hear that, you know?
attributes.name: Tatyana

attributes.content: Who cares.
attributes.name: Asbestos

attributes.content: *sigh* I actually planned to go out alone, if the Doctor hadn't insisted otherwise.
attributes.name: Tatyana

attributes.content: Buuuut, if you really aren't too keen to tag along with me, I could perhaps have a word with the Doctor...
attributes.name: Tatyana

attributes.content: Gah. Arghhhh. Alright, alright, we'll go together, yeah?
attributes.name: Asbestos

attributes.content: That's more like it!
attributes.name: Tatyana

attributes.content: Are we ready to go, ladies?
attributes.name: Pilot

attributes.content: Let's go!
attributes.name: Tatyana

attributes.content: *sigh*... I have a feeling this expedition is gonna be the second noisiest of my life.
attributes.name: Asbestos

attributes.content: Rosalind!
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Nothing here either. You... what's up?
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: ...Uh, forget about it.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Huh? But—
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: I lost. Mamochka's too crafty.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Tissue for you, Rosalind.
attributes.name: Gummy

attributes.content: I'm not crying though.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: I swore on that day to never cry again.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: I'll smash every annoying thing into bits with a smile on my face.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Hmph. Acting tough?
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: Yeah? Got a problem with that?
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Argh, let's get a move on already! It's chow time!
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Dinner's on me today, and I'll eat Mamochka's share too!
attributes.name: Leto
